La Pensée, la poésie et le politique (dialogue avec Jack Ralite)

   by Karelle Ménine & Jack Ralite
   devised and performed by Christian Gonon

   Studio
   April October 2020
   Available soon

   © c-album

   Studio

   La Pensée, la poésie et...

   2020-04-01 00:00:00 2020-10-31 00:00:00
   Available soon

   After performing at the Comédie-Française and touring a one-man show
   dedicated to Pierre Desproges for ten years, Christian Gonon has
   created a show in tribute to Jack Ralite, minister, member of
   parliament, senator, mayor of Aubervilliers, one-of-a-kind communist –
   “I write the word “communisthme” with “th”, like an isthmus, because
   that’s exactly what it is” – and theatre enthusiast.

   The creator of the États généraux de la Culture [National Culture
   Forum], who died in 2017, worked tirelessly to highlight the importance
   of culture as a crucible of social cohesion. For this production,
   Christian Gonon has adapted journalist Karelle Ménine’s book on Jack
   Ralite, which gathers interviews, texts and public speeches. The
   director explains his approach as follows:
   “Speaking Jack Ralite’s words is an act of resistance.
   Resistance to all forms of renunciation.
   Cultural, political, poetic...
   A powerful, full and generous resistance that draws its strength from a
   sensitive understanding of Humans.
   A resistance armed only with the spoken word and the clairvoyance of
   the poets.
   Their voices, which we no longer know how to hear.
   A companionship that raises us up to a higher level.
   Antoine Vitez spoke of the actor following in the poet’s footsteps,
   like a walker in the sand who places his feet in the footsteps of the
   person who went before him.
   So that time does not erase them.
   I try to retrace the paths of all Jack Ralite’s struggles, of all his
   acts of defiance, I slip into his thinking like a suit of light.
   At each crossroads I meet Aragon, Char, Hugo, Vilar, Saint-John Perse,
   Baudelaire....
   Whenever asked the recurrent question: ‘Why do you write?’, the poet’s
   answer will always be the shortest: ‘To live better’.”

   NEW PRODUCTION

   NOUVELLE PRODUCTION
   Venue
   -logo-2016-comedie-francaise-cmjn-studio-adresse-01

